sentences: Toshitsugu Nishihara (西原俊次, Nishihara Toshitsugu; born April 26, 1960) is a Japanese musician and composer, and the former keyboardist of Omega Tribe.

After the release of their debut single, "Summer Suspicion," the band had a successful career, with two of their singles, "Kimi no Heart wa Marine Blue" and "Futari no Natsu Monogatari" being their biggest hits.
In 1985, the band disbanded due to differences between the band and the producers.
In 1986, Fujita brought vocalist Carlos Toshiki and guitarist Mitsuya Kurokawa to create 1986 Omega Tribe, along with Nishihara and Takashima.
